14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Health
16 Care Authority, from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
17 General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the fiscal year
18 ending June 30, 2027, the sum of Two Million Five Hundred Thousand
19 Dollars ($2,500,000.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary to
20 provide a twenty-five percent (25%) rate increase for programs of
21 all-inclusive care for the elderly (PACE) for the purpose of
22 ensuring a more robust service delivery system for low-income and
23 aging Oklahomans.
24 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
Req. No. 3996 Page 1

1 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
2 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
3 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
4 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
